  "text": "Alter et al. first introduced a concept that orthogonal components (eigensystems) resulting from the singular value decomposition (SVD) of time-series gene expression dataset [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] may help to separate concurrent effects of different processes and regulators on gene expression. These authors proposed that an eigen array may reflect a genome-wide input from a particular regulator, with the corresponding eigen gene reflecting this regulator's activity across the samples (arrays). For an illustration of the SVD nomenclature, when applied to gene expression -see Additional file 1.",
